6// RemoveSwitchFallThrough.h: Remove fall-through from switch statements.
7// Note that it is unsafe to do further AST transformations on the AST generated
8// by this function. It leaves duplicate nodes in the AST making replacements
9// unreliable.
10
11#ifndef COMPILER_TRANSLATOR_TREEOPS_REMOVESWITCHFALLTHROUGH_H_
12#define COMPILER_TRANSLATOR_TREEOPS_REMOVESWITCHFALLTHROUGH_H_
13
14namespace sh
15{
16
17class TIntermBlock;
18class PerformanceDiagnostics;
19
20// When given a statementList from a switch AST node, return an updated
21// statementList that has fall-through removed.
22TIntermBlock *RemoveSwitchFallThrough(TIntermBlock *statementList,
23 PerformanceDiagnostics *perfDiagnostics);
24
25} // namespace sh
26
27#endif // COMPILER_TRANSLATOR_TREEOPS_REMOVESWITCHFALLTHROUGH_H_
